cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.AL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper presents a distributed self-adjusting algorithm for skip graphs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a new algorithm for skip graphs. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper deals with routing in skip graphs. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be relevant as skip graphs are used in peer-to-peer networks, but this is less likely as the paper focuses on the algorithmic aspect rather than the social aspect. 
- cs.AL (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper derives a lower bound for the routing cost of any algorithm conforming to their computational model.
